conditions.name: Admission Rescheduling Condition
conditions.description: Condition for rescheduling admission to the CRU on Day 1 if PG level is outside the specified range.
conditions.text: Admission can be rescheduled if PG level is not 90 to 250 mg/dL on Day 1.

conditions.name: Insulin Infusion Stop Condition
conditions.description: Condition to stop the insulin infusion procedure.
conditions.text: Insulin infusion is stopped once bedside PG is <60 mg/dL.

conditions.name: Interim Safety Review Trigger
conditions.description: The study will pause for a safety review after a specific number of patients have completed Period 2.
conditions.text: Safety data will be reviewed after the first 6 patients are administered LY900018 in Period 2, and the remaining patients will be dosed after confirmation of the safety.

conditions.name: Inadvertent Enrollment
conditions.description: Condition where a patient is found to not meet enrollment criteria after being enrolled.
conditions.text: The sponsor or investigator identifies a patient who did not meet enrollment criteria and was inadvertently enrolled.

conditions.name: TE ADA Positive at Follow-up
conditions.description: Condition for entering an additional follow-up period based on immunogenicity results.
conditions.text: Patients with TE ADA at follow-up/ED will undergo additional follow-up.

conditions.name: Patient Replacement Criteria
conditions.description: Criteria for replacing a discontinued patient.
conditions.text: If patients discontinue from the study before completion of both periods with evaluable primary outcome for any reason, the patient may be replaced.

transitionRules.name: Transition to Additional Follow-up
transitionRules.text: Patients with TE ADA at follow-up/ED will undergo additional follow-up.

transitionRules.name: Discontinuation of Inadvertently Enrolled Patient
transitionRules.text: If a patient is identified as inadvertently enrolled, a discussion must occur between the Lilly CP/CRP and the investigator to determine if the patient may continue in the study. If not approved, the patient will be discontinued.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Study Completion
scheduleTimelineExits.description: Patient has completed all protocol-required visits, including the final follow-up visit.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: End of Additional Follow-up
scheduleTimelineExits.description: Additional follow-up for immunogenicity ends when the titer returns to baseline or 1 year after the last dose of study treatment.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Withdrawal by Patient
scheduleTimelineExits.description: The patient, or legal representative, requests to be withdrawn from the study.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Investigator Decision
scheduleTimelineExits.description: The investigator decides that the patient should be discontinued from the study for any reason.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Medical, Safety, or Regulatory Reasons
scheduleTimelineExits.description: Participation in the study needs to be stopped for medical, safety, regulatory, or other reasons consistent with applicable laws, regulations, and good clinical practice.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Participation in Another Study
scheduleTimelineExits.description: Enrollment in any other clinical study involving an investigational product or enrollment in any other type of medical research judged not to be scientifically or medically compatible with this study.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Lost to Follow-up
scheduleTimelineExits.description: A patient will be considered lost to follow-up if he or she repeatedly fails to return for scheduled visits and is unable to be contacted by the study site.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Study Termination by Sponsor
scheduleTimelineExits.description: The study is stopped for patient safety in the opinion of the Investigator and sponsor following the interim safety review.

scheduledDecisionInstances.name: Interim Safety Review Decision
scheduledDecisionInstances.description: Decision point to continue or stop the study based on safety data from the first 6 patients who completed Period 2.

scheduledDecisionInstances.name: Additional Follow-up Decision
scheduledDecisionInstances.description: Decision to place a patient into an additional follow-up period based on TE ADA results at the follow-up visit.

scheduledDecisionInstances.name: Inadvertently Enrolled Patient Continuation Decision
scheduledDecisionInstances.description: Decision on whether an inadvertently enrolled patient can continue in the study, requiring documented approval from the Lilly CP/CRP.
